displayName: Bulk Corps Garrison Inn and Tavern 1F

parameters:
Skilled magician: 'Today, I defeated another incompetent
warrior in this town where many people underestimate
magic.'

The skilled magician says, 'A battle of mourning between
warriors is very welcome, you know?'

The skilled magician says, Hehe, it seems we can learn how
to escape from the warriors.

The skilled magician says, Oh, you've come without
hesitation! I'll show you real magic.

The skilled magician says, I don't want to admit that there
are warriors like you... but I'll accept defeat...

The skilled magician says, It's good that there's an inn
nearby.

Innkeeper: We don't have wine, but we can serve you the
best beer.

Innkeeper: We don't have wine, but I can offer you the best
beer.

Innkeeper: Have you ever been to Myukos? I want to see a
place that's bigger than the lake, the sea!

Farmer Man: Have you had the beer? It seems like the
quality is pretty good this year.

Drunk customer: Glory to the Bulk Brigade! We are the
greatest warriors, the chosen ones loved by the goddess
Actina!

Oh, it's you guys from the Bulk Gang! Why don't you come
over here and have a drink with us!

Cleric Sophia: Hehe, I would be delighted to accompany
you.

Cleric Sophia: By the way... Have you heard the rumors
about the appearance of a werewolf?

Bulk Gang's Goat: 'Do werewolves really exist? Hahaha, it's
amusing coming from a man who almost turned into an orc!'

Bulk Gang's Goat: It's a serious matter, but if werewolves
really exist, there should definitely be reports from
someone.

Bulk Gang's Goat: If you need any help, make sure to let us
know. We'll definitely repay you guys a little!

Bulk Gang's Goat: I see, Stasis... He's the man who started
talking after interacting with you guys.

Bulk Gang's Goat: I hear he often has nightmares. Well, it
seems like this is not something new.

Bulk Gang's Goat: I've got an idea! How about we provide
security for him? That way, he can sleep peacefully.
Bulk Gang's Goat: Once you guys are ready, please join us!

Cleric Sophia: Oh my, I hope Mr. Goat's departure doesn't
end up being counterproductive...

Clea: Wouldn't it be reassuring if we had a hero like
Valt?

Cleric Sophia: Hehe, Clea-chan is on that side too, isn't
she?
Cleric Sophia: Hehe, I thought it would be about time.

Mage Stasis: I appreciate the kindness, but I won't be able
to sleep if the men are banging axes and shields.

Mage Stasis: Well, I can't sleep in the first place...
Lately, I've been forcing myself with alcohol, so to speak.

Cleric Sophia: I heard you've been researching the demons
of nightmares, is that true?

Mage Stasis: Yes, originally I was researching that. As for
the demons of transformation, I've only recently started
studying them.

Mage Stasis: When I was five years old, my mother abandoned
me because I was getting in the way of her remarriage... But
even now, I can't bring myself to hate her.

Mage Stasis: Since then, I've been dealing with nightmares,
so I became a mage and started researching the demons of
nightmares.

Mage Stasis: I'm currently researching about the
transformation of dreams. It's strange, isn't it? I can talk
about anything when I'm with you.
Cleric Sophia: Oh my, are you being flirted with?

Mage Stasis: N-No, that's not it! I just feel like you
somehow understand me...

Mage Stasis: C-Can I sleep for a little while? It's safe to
sleep here since the werewolves won't come...

Cleric Sophia: Yes, I understand. I've been having
nightmares for a long time too...
Cleric Sophia: T-This is... Mage Stasis!?

Cleric Sophia: I have to go tell Clea-chan and the others
about the true identity of the werewolves!
